{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["47-2CO-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"2CO"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["2 Corinthians \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Paul’s Second Letter to the Corinthians \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["2 Corinthians \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["2Co \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Paul’s Second Letter to the Corinthians \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"2CO 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 1:1"},"Paul, an apostle of Masih Isa through the will of Allah, and Timothy our brother, to the assembly of Allah which is at\nCorinth, with all the saints who are in the whole of Achaia: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 1:2"},"Grace to you and peace from Allah our Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 1:3"},"Blessed be Allah and Father of our Lord Al Masih Isa, the Father of mercies and Allah of all comfort;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 1:4"},"who comforts us in all our affliction, that we may be able to comfort those who are in any affliction, through the comfort\nwith which we ourselves are comforted by Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 1:5"},"For as the sufferings of Masih abound to us, even so our comfort also abounds through Masih.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 1:6"},"But if we are afflicted, it is for your comfort and salvation. If we are comforted, it is for your comfort, which produces\nin you the patient enduring of the same sufferings which we also suffer.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 1:7"},"Our hope for you is steadfast, knowing that, since you are partakers of the sufferings, so you are also of the comfort.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 1:8"},"For we don’t desire to have you uninformed, brothers,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:8\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “brothers” here and where context allows may also be correctly translated “brothers and sisters” or\n“siblings.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," concerning our affliction which happened to us in Asia, that we were weighed down exceedingly, beyond our power,\nso much that we despaired even of life. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 1:9"},"Yes, we ourselves have had the sentence of death within ourselves, that we should not trust in ourselves, but in Allah who\nraises the dead, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 1:10"},"who delivered us out of so great a death, and does deliver; on whom we have set our hope that he will also still deliver\nus; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 1:11"},"you also helping together on our behalf by your supplication; that, for the gift given to us by means of many, thanks may\nbe given by many persons on your behalf. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 1:12"},"For our boasting is this: the testimony of our conscience, that in holiness and sincerity of Allah, not in fleshly wisdom\nbut in the grace of Allah we behaved ourselves in the world, and more abundantly towards you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 1:13"},"For we write no other things to you than what you read or even acknowledge, and I hope you will acknowledge to the end,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 1:14"},"as also you acknowledged us in part, that we are your boasting, even as you also are ours, in the day of our Lord Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 1:15"},"In this confidence, I was determined to come first to you, that you might have a second benefit,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 1:16"},"and by you to pass into Macedonia, and again from Macedonia to come to you, and to be sent forward by you on my journey\nto Judea. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 1:17"},"When I therefore was thus determined, did I show fickleness? Or the things that I purpose, do I purpose according to the\nflesh, that with me there should be the “Yes, yes” and the “No, no?”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 1:18"},"But as Allah is faithful, our word towards you was not “Yes and no.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CO 1:19"},"For the Son of Allah, Al Masih Isa, who was preached amongst you by us, by me, Silvanus, and Timothy, was not “Yes and\nno,” but in him is “Yes.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CO 1:20"},"For however many are the promises of Allah, in him is the “Yes.” Therefore also through him is the “Amen”, to the glory\nof Allah through us. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CO 1:21"},"Now he who establishes us with you in Masih and anointed us is Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CO 1:22"},"who also sealed us, and gave us the down payment of the Spirit in our hearts.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CO 1:23"},"But I call Allah for a witness to my soul, that I didn’t come to Corinth to spare you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CO 1:24"},"We don’t control your faith, but are fellow workers with you for your joy. For you stand firm in faith.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"2CO 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 2:1"},"But I determined this for myself, that I would not come to you again in sorrow.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 2:2"},"For if I make you grieve, then who will make me glad but he who is made to grieve by me?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 2:3"},"And I wrote this very thing to you, so that, when I came, I wouldn’t have sorrow from them of whom I ought to rejoice;\nhaving confidence in you all, that my joy would be shared by all of you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 2:4"},"For out of much affliction and anguish of heart I wrote to you with many tears, not that you should be made to grieve, but\nthat you might know the love that I have so abundantly for you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 2:5"},"But if any has caused sorrow, he has caused sorrow, not to me, but in part (that I not press too heavily) to you all.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 2:6"},"This punishment which was inflicted by the many is sufficient for such a one;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 2:7"},"so that on the contrary you should rather forgive him and comfort him, lest by any means such a one should be swallowed up\nwith his excessive sorrow. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 2:8"},"Therefore I beg you to confirm your love towards him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 2:9"},"For to this end I also wrote, that I might know the proof of you, whether you are obedient in all things.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 2:10"},"Now I also forgive whomever you forgive anything. For if indeed I have forgiven anything, I have forgiven that one for\nyour sakes in the presence of Masih, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 2:11"},"that no advantage may be gained over us by Iblis, for we are not ignorant of his schemes.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 2:12"},"Now when I came to Troas for the Good News of Masih, and when a door was opened to me in the Lord,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 2:13"},"I had no relief for my spirit, because I didn’t find Titus, my brother, but taking my leave of them, I went out into\nMacedonia. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 2:14"},"Now thanks be to Allah, who always leads us in triumph in Masih, and reveals through us the sweet aroma of his knowledge\nin every place. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 2:15"},"For we are a sweet aroma of Masih to Allah, in those who are saved and in those who perish:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 2:16"},"to the one a stench from death to death, to the other a sweet aroma from life to life. Who is sufficient for these\nthings? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 2:17"},"For we are not as so many, peddling the word of Allah. But as of sincerity, but as of Allah, in the sight of Allah, we\nspeak in Masih. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"2CO 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 3:1"},"Are we beginning again to commend ourselves? Or do we need, as do some, letters of commendation to you or from you?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 3:2"},"You are our letter, written in our hearts, known and read by all men,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 3:3"},"being revealed that you are a letter of Masih, served by us, written not with ink, but with the Spirit of the living\nAllah; not in tablets of stone, but in tablets that are hearts of flesh.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 3:4"},"Such confidence we have through Masih towards Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 3:5"},"not that we are sufficient of ourselves, to account anything as from ourselves; but our sufficiency is from Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 3:6"},"who also made us sufficient as servants of a new covenant, not of the letter, but of the Spirit. For the letter kills, but\nthe Spirit gives life. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 3:7"},"But if the service of death, written engraved on stones, came with glory, so that the children of Israel could not look\nsteadfastly on the face of Musa for the glory of his face, which was passing away,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 3:8"},"won’t service of the Spirit be with much more glory? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 3:9"},"For if the service of condemnation has glory, the service of righteousness exceeds much more in glory.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 3:10"},"For most certainly that which has been made glorious has not been made glorious in this respect, by reason of the glory\nthat surpasses. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 3:11"},"For if that which passes away was with glory, much more that which remains is in glory.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 3:12"},"Having therefore such a hope, we use great boldness of speech,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 3:13"},"and not as Musa, who put a veil on his face, that the children of Israel wouldn’t look steadfastly on the end of that\nwhich was passing away. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 3:14"},"But their minds were hardened, for until this very day at the reading of the old covenant the same veil remains, because\nin Masih it passes away. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 3:15"},"But to this day, when Musa is read, a veil lies on their heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 3:16"},"But whenever someone turns to the Lord, the veil is taken away.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 3:17"},"Now the Lord is the Spirit and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is liberty.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 3:18"},"But we all, with unveiled face seeing the glory of the Lord as in a mirror, are transformed into the same image from\nglory to glory, even as from the Lord, the Spirit. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"2CO 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 4:1"},"Therefore seeing we have this ministry, even as we obtained mercy, we don’t faint.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 4:2"},"But we have renounced the hidden things of shame, not walking in craftiness, nor handling the word of Allah deceitfully,\nbut by the manifestation of the truth commending ourselves to every man’s conscience in the sight of Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 4:3"},"Even if our Good News is veiled, it is veiled in those who are dying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 4:4"},"in whom the god of this world has blinded the minds of the unbelieving, that the light of the Good News of the glory of\nMasih, who is the image of Allah, should not dawn on them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 4:5"},"For we don’t preach ourselves, but Masih Isa as Lord, and ourselves as your servants for Isa’s sake,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 4:6"},"seeing it is Allah who said, “Light will shine out of darkness,”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Genesis 1:3"]}],"caller":"+"}," who has shone in our hearts to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of Allah in the face of\nAl Masih Isa. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 4:7"},"But we have this treasure in clay vessels, that the exceeding greatness of the power may be of Allah, and not from\nourselves. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 4:8"},"We are pressed on every side, yet not crushed; perplexed, yet not to despair;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 4:9"},"pursued, yet not forsaken; struck down, yet not destroyed; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 4:10"},"always carrying in the body the putting to death of the Lord Isa, that the life of Isa may also be revealed in our body.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 4:11"},"For we who live are always delivered to death for Isa’s sake, that the life also of Isa may be revealed in our mortal\nflesh. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 4:12"},"So then death works in us, but life in you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 4:13"},"But having the same spirit of faith, according to that which is written, “I believed, and therefore I\nspoke.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 116:10"]}],"caller":"+"}," We also believe, and therefore we also speak;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 4:14"},"knowing that he who raised the Lord Isa will raise us also with Isa, and will present us with you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 4:15"},"For all things are for your sakes, that the grace, being multiplied through the many, may cause the thanksgiving to\nabound to the glory of Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 4:16"},"Therefore we don’t faint, but though our outward man is decaying, yet our inward man is renewed day by day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 4:17"},"For our light affliction, which is for the moment, works for us more and more exceedingly an eternal weight of glory,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 4:18"},"while we don’t look at the things which are seen, but at the things which are not seen. For the things which are seen are\ntemporal, but the things which are not seen are eternal. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"2CO 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 5:1"},"For we know that if the earthly house of our tent is dissolved, we have a building from Allah, a house not made with\nhands, eternal, in the heavens. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 5:2"},"For most certainly in this we groan, longing to be clothed with our habitation which is from heaven,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 5:3"},"if indeed being clothed, we will not be found naked. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 5:4"},"For indeed we who are in this tent do groan, being burdened, not that we desire to be unclothed, but that we desire to be\nclothed, that what is mortal may be swallowed up by life. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 5:5"},"Now he who made us for this very thing is Allah, who also gave to us the down payment of the Spirit.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 5:6"},"Therefore we are always confident and know that while we are at home in the body, we are absent from the Lord;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 5:7"},"for we walk by faith, not by sight. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 5:8"},"We are courageous, I say, and are willing rather to be absent from the body and to be at home with the Lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 5:9"},"Therefore also we make it our aim, whether at home or absent, to be well pleasing to him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 5:10"},"For we must all be revealed before the judgement seat of Masih that each one may receive the things in the body according\nto what he has done, whether good or bad. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 5:11"},"Knowing therefore the fear of the Lord, we persuade men, but we are revealed to Allah, and I hope that we are revealed\nalso in your consciences. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 5:12"},"For we are not commending ourselves to you again, but speak as giving you occasion of boasting on our behalf, that you\nmay have something to answer those who boast in appearance, and not in heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 5:13"},"For if we are beside ourselves, it is for Allah. Or if we are of sober mind, it is for you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 5:14"},"For the love of Masih constrains us; because we judge thus, that one died for all, therefore all died.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 5:15"},"He died for all, that those who live should no longer live to themselves, but to him who for their sakes died and rose\nagain. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 5:16"},"Therefore we know no one after the flesh from now on. Even though we have known Masih after the flesh, yet now we know\nhim so no more. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 5:17"},"Therefore if anyone is in Masih, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away.\nBehold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “ἰδοὺ”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," all things have become new. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 5:18"},"But all things are of Allah, who reconciled us to himself through Al Masih Isa, and gave to us the ministry of\nreconciliation; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CO 5:19"},"namely, that Allah was in Masih reconciling the world to himself, not reckoning to them their trespasses, and having\ncommitted to us the word of reconciliation. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CO 5:20"},"We are therefore ambassadors on behalf of Masih, as though Allah were entreating by us: we beg you on behalf of Masih, be\nreconciled to Allah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CO 5:21"},"For him who knew no sin he made to be sin on our behalf; so that in him we might become the righteousness of Allah.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"2CO 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 6:1"},"Working together, we entreat also that you do not receive the grace of Allah in vain,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 6:2"},"for he says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“At an acceptable time I listened to you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["In a day of salvation I helped you.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah\n49:8"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Behold, now is the acceptable time. Behold, now is the day of salvation.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 6:3"},"We give no occasion of stumbling in anything, that our service may not be blamed,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 6:4"},"but in everything commending ourselves, as servants of Allah, in great endurance, in afflictions, in hardships, in\ndistresses, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 6:5"},"in beatings, in imprisonments, in riots, in labours, in watchings, in fastings;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 6:6"},"in pureness, in knowledge, in perseverance, in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in sincere love,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 6:7"},"in the word of truth, in the power of Allah; by the armour of righteousness on the right hand and on the left,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 6:8"},"by glory and dishonour, by evil report and good report; as deceivers, and yet true;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 6:9"},"as unknown, and yet well known; as dying, and behold, we live; as punished, and not killed;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 6:10"},"as sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing all things.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 6:11"},"Our mouth is open to you, Corinthians. Our heart is enlarged.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 6:12"},"You are not restricted by us, but you are restricted by your own affections.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 6:13"},"Now in return, I speak as to my children: you also open your hearts.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 6:14"},"Don’t be unequally yoked with unbelievers, for what fellowship do righteousness and iniquity have? Or what fellowship\ndoes light have with darkness? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 6:15"},"What agreement does Masih have with Belial? Or what portion does a believer have with an unbeliever?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 6:16"},"What agreement does a temple of Allah have with idols? For you are a temple of the living Allah. Even as Allah said, “I\nwill dwell in them and walk in them. I will be their Allah and they will be my\npeople.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 26:12; Jeremiah 32:38; Ezekiel\n37:27"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 6:17"},"Therefore \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“‘Come out from amongst them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and be separate,’ says the Lord. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Touch no unclean thing. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will receive you.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 52:11; Ezekiel 20:34,41"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 6:18"},"I will be to you a Father. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You will be to me sons and daughters,’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["says the Lord Almighty.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Samuel 7:14; 7:8"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"2CO 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 7:1"},"Having therefore these promises, beloved, let’s cleanse ourselves from all defilement of flesh and spirit, perfecting\nholiness in the fear of Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 7:2"},"Open your hearts to us. We wronged no one. We corrupted no one. We took advantage of no one.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 7:3"},"I say this not to condemn you, for I have said before that you are in our hearts to die together and live together.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 7:4"},"Great is my boldness of speech towards you. Great is my boasting on your behalf. I am filled with comfort. I overflow with\njoy in all our affliction. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 7:5"},"For even when we had come into Macedonia, our flesh had no relief, but we were afflicted on every side. Fightings were\noutside. Fear was inside. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 7:6"},"Nevertheless, he who comforts the lowly, Allah, comforted us by the coming of Titus,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 7:7"},"and not by his coming only, but also by the comfort with which he was comforted in you while he told us of your longing,\nyour mourning, and your zeal for me, so that I rejoiced still more.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 7:8"},"For though I grieved you with my letter, I do not regret it, though I did regret it. For I see that my letter made you\ngrieve, though just for a while. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 7:9"},"I now rejoice, not that you were grieved, but that you were grieved to repentance. For you were grieved in a godly way,\nthat you might suffer loss by us in nothing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 7:10"},"For godly sorrow produces repentance to salvation, which brings no regret. But the sorrow of the world produces death.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 7:11"},"For behold, this same thing, that you were grieved in a godly way, what earnest care it worked in you. Yes, what defence,\nindignation, fear, longing, zeal, and vengeance! In everything you demonstrated yourselves to be pure in the matter.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 7:12"},"So although I wrote to you, I wrote not for his cause that did the wrong, nor for his cause that suffered the wrong, but\nthat your earnest care for us might be revealed in you in the sight of Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 7:13"},"Therefore we have been comforted. In our comfort we rejoiced the more exceedingly for the joy of Titus, because his\nspirit has been refreshed by you all. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 7:14"},"For if in anything I have boasted to him on your behalf, I was not disappointed. But as we spoke all things to you in\ntruth, so our glorying also which I made before Titus was found to be truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 7:15"},"His affection is more abundantly towards you, while he remembers all of your obedience, how with fear and trembling you\nreceived him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 7:16"},"I rejoice that in everything I am confident concerning you.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"2CO 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 8:1"},"Moreover, brothers, we make known to you the grace of Allah which has been given in the assemblies of Macedonia,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 8:2"},"how in much proof of affliction, the abundance of their joy and their deep poverty abounded to the riches of their\ngenerosity. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 8:3"},"For according to their power, I testify, yes and beyond their power, they gave of their own accord,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 8:4"},"begging us with much entreaty to receive this grace and the fellowship in the service to the saints.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 8:5"},"This was not as we had expected, but first they gave their own selves to the Lord, and to us through the will of Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 8:6"},"So we urged Titus, that as he had made a beginning before, so he would also complete in you this grace.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 8:7"},"But as you abound in everything, in faith, utterance, knowledge, all earnestness, and in your love to us, see that you\nalso abound in this grace. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 8:8"},"I speak not by way of commandment, but as proving through the earnestness of others the sincerity also of your love.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 8:9"},"For you know the grace of our Lord Al Masih Isa, that though he was rich, yet for your sakes he became poor, that you\nthrough his poverty might become rich. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 8:10"},"I give a judgement in this: for this is expedient for you who were the first to start a year ago, not only to do, but\nalso to be willing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 8:11"},"But now complete the doing also, that as there was the readiness to be willing, so there may be the completion also out\nof your ability. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 8:12"},"For if the readiness is there, it is acceptable according to what you have, not according to what you don’t have.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 8:13"},"For this is not that others may be eased and you distressed,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 8:14"},"but for equality. Your abundance at this present time supplies their lack, that their abundance also may become a supply\nfor your lack; that there may be equality. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 8:15"},"As it is written, “He who gathered much had nothing left over, and he who gathered little had no\nlack.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 16:18"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 8:16"},"But thanks be to Allah, who puts the same earnest care for you into the heart of Titus.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 8:17"},"For he indeed accepted our exhortation, but being himself very earnest, he went out to you of his own accord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 8:18"},"We have sent together with him the brother whose praise in the Good News is known throughout all the assemblies.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CO 8:19"},"Not only so, but he was also appointed by the assemblies to travel with us in this grace, which is served by us to the\nglory of the Lord himself, and to show our readiness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CO 8:20"},"We are avoiding this, that any man should blame us concerning this abundance which is administered by us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CO 8:21"},"Having regard for honourable things, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of men.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CO 8:22"},"We have sent with them our brother, whom we have many times proved earnest in many things, but now much more earnest, by\nreason of the great confidence which he has in you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CO 8:23"},"As for Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker for you. As for our brothers, they are the apostles of the assemblies,\nthe glory of Masih. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CO 8:24"},"Therefore show the proof of your love to them before the assemblies, and of our boasting on your behalf.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"2CO 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 9:1"},"It is indeed unnecessary for me to write to you concerning the service to the saints,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 9:2"},"for I know your readiness, of which I boast on your behalf to those of Macedonia, that Achaia has been prepared for the\npast year. Your zeal has stirred up very many of them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 9:3"},"But I have sent the brothers that our boasting on your behalf may not be in vain in this respect, that, just as I said,\nyou may be prepared, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 9:4"},"lest by any means, if anyone from Macedonia comes there with me and finds you unprepared, we (to say nothing of you) would\nbe disappointed in this confident boasting. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 9:5"},"I thought it necessary therefore to entreat the brothers that they would go before to you and arrange ahead of time the\ngenerous gift that you promised before, that the same might be ready as a matter of generosity, and not of greediness.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 9:6"},"Remember this: he who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly. He who sows bountifully will also reap bountifully.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 9:7"},"Let each man give according as he has determined in his heart, not grudgingly or under compulsion. for Allah loves a\ncheerful giver. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 9:8"},"And Allah is able to make all grace abound to you, that you, always having all sufficiency in everything, may abound to\nevery good work. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 9:9"},"As it is written, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“He has scattered abroad. He has given to the poor. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["His righteousness remains forever.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["9:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 112:9"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 9:10"},"Now may he who supplies seed to the sower and bread for food, supply and multiply your seed for sowing, and increase the\nfruits of your righteousness, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 9:11"},"you being enriched in everything to all generosity, which produces thanksgiving to Allah through us.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 9:12"},"For this service of giving that you perform not only makes up for lack amongst the saints, but abounds also through much\ngiving of thanks to Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 9:13"},"seeing that through the proof given by this service, they glorify Allah for the obedience of your confession to the Good\nNews of Masih and for the generosity of your contribution to them and to all,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 9:14"},"while they themselves also, with supplication on your behalf, yearn for you by reason of the exceeding grace of Allah in\nyou. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 9:15"},"Now thanks be to Allah for his unspeakable gift! \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"2CO 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 10:1"},"Now I Paul, myself, entreat you by the humility and gentleness of Masih, I who in your presence am lowly amongst you, but\nbeing absent am bold towards you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 10:2"},"Yes, I beg you that I may not, when present, show courage with the confidence with which I intend to be bold against some,\nwho consider us to be walking according to the flesh. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 10:3"},"For though we walk in the flesh, we don’t wage war according to the flesh;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 10:4"},"for the weapons of our warfare are not of the flesh, but mighty before Allah to the throwing down of strongholds,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 10:5"},"throwing down imaginations and every high thing that is exalted against the knowledge of Allah and bringing every thought\ninto captivity to the obedience of Masih, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 10:6"},"and being in readiness to avenge all disobedience when your obedience is made full.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 10:7"},"Do you look at things only as they appear in front of your face? If anyone trusts in himself that he is Masih’s, let him\nconsider this again with himself, that even as he is Masih’s, so we also are Masih’s.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 10:8"},"For even if I boast somewhat abundantly concerning our authority, which the Lord gave for building you up, and not for\ncasting you down, I will not be ashamed, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 10:9"},"that I may not seem as if I desire to terrify you by my letters.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 10:10"},"For, “His letters”, they say, “are weighty and strong, but his bodily presence is weak, and his speech is despised.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 10:11"},"Let such a person consider this, that what we are in word by letters when we are absent, such are we also in deed when we\nare present. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 10:12"},"For we are not bold to number or compare ourselves with some of those who commend themselves. But they themselves,\nmeasuring themselves by themselves, and comparing themselves with themselves, are without understanding.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 10:13"},"But we will not boast beyond proper limits, but within the boundaries with which Allah appointed to us, which reach even\nto you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 10:14"},"For we don’t stretch ourselves too much, as though we didn’t reach to you. For we came even as far as to you with the\nGood News of Masih, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 10:15"},"not boasting beyond proper limits in other men’s labours, but having hope that as your faith grows, we will be abundantly\nenlarged by you in our sphere of influence, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 10:16"},"so as to preach the Good News even to the parts beyond you, not to boast in what someone else has already done.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 10:17"},"But “he who boasts, let him boast in the Lord.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:17\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 9:24 "]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 10:18"},"For it isn’t he who commends himself who is approved, but whom the Lord commends.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"2CO 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 11:1"},"I wish that you would bear with me in a little foolishness, but indeed you do bear with me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 11:2"},"For I am jealous over you with a godly jealousy. For I married you to one husband, that I might present you as a pure\nvirgin to Masih. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 11:3"},"But I am afraid that somehow, as the serpent deceived Havva in his craftiness, so your minds might be corrupted from the\nsimplicity that is in Masih. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 11:4"},"For if he who comes preaches another Isa, whom we didn’t preach, or if you receive a different spirit, which you didn’t\nreceive, or a different “good news”, which you didn’t accept, you put up with that well enough.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 11:5"},"For I reckon that I am not at all behind the very best apostles.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 11:6"},"But though I am unskilled in speech, yet I am not unskilled in knowledge. No, in every way we have been revealed to you in\nall things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 11:7"},"Or did I commit a sin in humbling myself that you might be exalted, because I preached to you Allah’s Good News free of\ncharge? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 11:8"},"I robbed other assemblies, taking wages from them that I might serve you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 11:9"},"When I was present with you and was in need, I wasn’t a burden on anyone, for the brothers, when they came from Macedonia,\nsupplied the measure of my need. In everything I kept myself from being burdensome to you, and I will continue to do so.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 11:10"},"As the truth of Masih is in me, no one will stop me from this boasting in the regions of Achaia.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 11:11"},"Why? Because I don’t love you? Allah knows. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 11:12"},"But what I do, that I will do, that I may cut off occasion from those who desire an occasion, that in which they boast,\nthey may be found even as we. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 11:13"},"For such men are false apostles, deceitful workers, masquerading as Masih’s apostles.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 11:14"},"And no wonder, for even Iblis masquerades as an angel of light.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 11:15"},"It is no great thing therefore if his servants also masquerade as servants of righteousness, whose end will be according\nto their works. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 11:16"},"I say again, let no one think me foolish. But if so, yet receive me as foolish, that I also may boast a little.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 11:17"},"That which I speak, I don’t speak according to the Lord, but as in foolishness, in this confidence of boasting.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 11:18"},"Seeing that many boast after the flesh, I will also boast.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CO 11:19"},"For you bear with the foolish gladly, being wise. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CO 11:20"},"For you bear with a man if he brings you into bondage, if he devours you, if he takes you captive, if he exalts himself,\nor if he strikes you on the face. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CO 11:21"},"I speak by way of disparagement, as though we had been weak. Yet in whatever way anyone is bold (I speak in foolishness),\nI am bold also. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2CO 11:22"},"Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they the\noffspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," of Ibrahim? So am I. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2CO 11:23"},"Are they servants of Masih? (I speak as one beside himself.) I am more so: in labours more abundantly, in prisons more\nabundantly, in stripes above measure, and in deaths often. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2CO 11:24"},"Five times I received forty stripes minus one from the Jews.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2CO 11:25"},"Three times I was beaten with rods. Once I was stoned. Three times I suffered shipwreck. I have been a night and a day in\nthe deep. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2CO 11:26"},"I have been in travels often, perils of rivers, perils of robbers, perils from my countrymen, perils from the Gentiles,\nperils in the city, perils in the wilderness, perils in the sea, perils amongst false brothers;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"2CO 11:27"},"in labour and travail, in watchings often, in hunger and thirst, in fastings often, and in cold and nakedness.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"2CO 11:28"},"Besides those things that are outside, there is that which presses on me daily: anxiety for all the assemblies.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"2CO 11:29"},"Who is weak, and I am not weak? Who is caused to stumble, and I don’t burn with indignation?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"2CO 11:30"},"If I must boast, I will boast of the things that concern my weakness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"2CO 11:31"},"The Allah and Father of the Lord Al Masih Isa, he who is blessed forever more, knows that I don’t lie.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"2CO 11:32"},"In Damascus the governor under King Aretas guarded the Damascenes’ city, desiring to arrest me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"2CO 11:33"},"I was let down in a basket through a window by the wall, and escaped his hands.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"2CO 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 12:1"},"It is doubtless not profitable for me to boast. For I will come to visions and revelations of the Lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 12:2"},"I know a man in Masih, fourteen years ago (whether in the body, I don’t know, or whether out of the body, I don’t know;\nAllah knows), such a one caught up into the third heaven. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 12:3"},"I know such a man (whether in the body, or outside of the body, I don’t know; Allah knows),\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 12:4"},"how he was caught up into Paradise, and heard unspeakable words, which it is not lawful for a man to utter.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 12:5"},"On behalf of such a one I will boast, but on my own behalf I will not boast, except in my weaknesses.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 12:6"},"For if I would desire to boast, I will not be foolish; for I will speak the truth. But I refrain, so that no man may think\nmore of me than that which he sees in me or hears from me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 12:7"},"By reason of the exceeding greatness of the revelations, that I should not be exalted excessively, a thorn in the flesh\nwas given to me: a messenger of Iblis to torment me, that I should not be exalted excessively.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 12:8"},"Concerning this thing, I begged the Lord three times that it might depart from me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 12:9"},"He has said to me, ",{"type":"char","marker":"wj","content":["“My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in\nweakness.”"]}," Most gladly therefore I will rather glory in my weaknesses, that the power of Masih may rest on me.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 12:10"},"Therefore I take pleasure in weaknesses, in injuries, in necessities, in persecutions, and in distresses, for Masih’s\nsake. For when I am weak, then am I strong. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 12:11"},"I have become foolish in boasting. You compelled me, for I ought to have been commended by you, for in nothing was I\ninferior to the very best apostles, though I am nothing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 12:12"},"Truly the signs of an apostle were worked amongst you in all perseverance, in signs and wonders and mighty works.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 12:13"},"For what is there in which you were made inferior to the rest of the assemblies, unless it is that I myself was not a\nburden to you? Forgive me this wrong. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 12:14"},"Behold, this is the third time I am ready to come to you, and I will not be a burden to you; for I seek not your\npossessions, but you. For the children ought not to save up for the parents, but the parents for the children.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2CO 12:15"},"I will most gladly spend and be spent for your souls. If I love you more abundantly, am I loved the less?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2CO 12:16"},"Even so, I myself didn’t burden you. “But, being crafty, I caught you with deception.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2CO 12:17"},"Did I take advantage of you by anyone of those whom I have sent to you?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2CO 12:18"},"I exhorted Titus, and I sent the brother with him. Did Titus take any advantage of you? Didn’t we walk in the same\nspirit? Didn’t we walk in the same steps? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2CO 12:19"},"Again, do you think that we are excusing ourselves to you? In the sight of Allah we speak in Masih. But all things,\nbeloved, are for your edifying. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2CO 12:20"},"For I am afraid that by any means, when I come, I might find you not the way I want to, and that I might be found by you\nas you don’t desire, that by any means there would be strife, jealousy, outbursts of anger, factions, slander, whisperings,\nproud thoughts, or riots, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2CO 12:21"},"that again when I come my Allah would humble me before you, and I would mourn for many of those who have sinned before\nnow, and not repented of the uncleanness, sexual immorality, and lustfulness which they committed.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"2CO 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2CO 13:1"},"This is the third time I am coming to you. “At the mouth of two or three witnesses shall every word be\nestablished.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["13:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 19:15"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2CO 13:2"},"I have said beforehand, and I do say beforehand, as when I was present the second time, so now, being absent, I write to\nthose who have sinned before now, and to all the rest, that, if I come again, I will not spare;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2CO 13:3"},"seeing that you seek a proof of Masih who speaks in me; who towards you is not weak, but is powerful in you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2CO 13:4"},"For he was crucified through weakness, yet he lives through the power of Allah. For we also are weak in him, but we will\nlive with him through the power of Allah towards you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2CO 13:5"},"Examine your own selves, whether you are in the faith. Test your own selves. Or don’t you know about your own selves, that\nAl Masih Isa is in you?—unless indeed you are disqualified. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2CO 13:6"},"But I hope that you will know that we aren’t disqualified. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2CO 13:7"},"Now I pray to Allah that you do no evil; not that we may appear approved, but that you may do that which is honourable,\nthough we are as reprobate. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2CO 13:8"},"For we can do nothing against the truth, but for the truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2CO 13:9"},"For we rejoice when we are weak and you are strong. We also pray for this: your becoming perfect.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2CO 13:10"},"For this cause I write these things while absent, that I may not deal sharply when present, according to the authority\nwhich the Lord gave me for building up, and not for tearing down.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2CO 13:11"},"Finally, brothers, rejoice! Be perfected. Be comforted. Be of the same mind. Live in peace, and Allah of love and peace\nwill be with you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2CO 13:12"},"Greet one another with a holy kiss. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2CO 13:13"},"All the saints greet you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2CO 13:14"},"The grace of the Lord Al Masih Isa, Allah’s love, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit be with you all. Amen.\n"]}]}